s M.Ed (Ed.Education) and is a Member of Nigeria Institute of Management  (MNIM). He takes over from Mrs Ifeoma Ezeokoli who had been in acting capacity. Speaking on the appointment, the chairman of the governing council of the polytechnic, Malam Kale Kawu expressed satisfaction with the process  leading to the emergence of the Registrar and commended the selection board committee for discharging its task with tact and dedication. Malam Kawu, who described registry department as the engine room of the polytechnic, urged the new Registrar to bring his wealth of experience to bear in his new assignment and add great value to the progress of the polytechnic. He also called for co-operation and support for the Registrar  from the management and members of staff of the institution.    By Adeola Badru Governing Council of the newly-established Federal Polytechnic, Ayede (FEDPA),Oyo State, has sought the support of all key stakeholders for the smooth take-off of the institution. The governing council sought the support while meeting with host communities in Ogbomosoland during its on-the-spot assessment of the facilities in the… In "News" The Non-Academic Staff of the Federal University of Technology, Akure, FUTA, have expressed satisfaction with the processes that led to the appointment of the first female Vice Chancellor of the institution, Professor (Mrs) Adenike Temidayo Oladiji. In "News" Join cult, lose your admission, Oko Poly Rector tells students In "News"